"title": "STAINLESS STEEL CROWN (SSC) — SSC: note template",
"body": "SSC: note template\n - y/o female presents to UG Peds with mother for #A SSC\n - RMH with mother. No changes.\n - allergies:, no medications, IUTD\n\n Titrated to 40% nitrous oxide / 60% oxygen at 4L/min. Administered for 90 minutes. Applied 20% topical benzocaine & administered 1 carpule of\n 2% lidocaine 1:100k epi as IAN & long buccal block on right / buccal infiltration #A.\n\n #A SSC\n Placed bite block & Isodry placed (size P). Completely removed failing existing MOD resin composite restoration & excavated D decay\n using high & slow speed burs. Completed crown prep to ideal form. Tried on SSC [ size ]; trimmed & crimped to ideal fit. Confirmed occlusion. Placed throat-pack gauze. Cemented crown with FujiCEM & seated using a bite stick. Excess cement cleaned, flossed.\n Re-confirmed occlusion.\n\n Patient given 100% oxygen at 4L/min for 5 minutes. Patient released in good condition. Informed mother that pt is still numb, monitor lip & soft\n tissue biting.\n\n - behavior: F[ 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 ]\n - NV: 6 month recall\n - [Student Name] / Dr. [Instructor]"
