 description: "Multiple lost teeth, failing existing restorations, untreated endo issues, occlusal collapse — a months-long phased treatment plan. Phase 1 is disease control (caries excavation, endo, perio scaling). Phase 2 establishes the prosthetic foundation (extractions, ridge preservation, provisional restorations at the new VDO if needed). Phase 3 is the definitive restorative work in mounted-cast sequence. The diagnostic wax-up done up front is the single highest-yield investment in the whole case.",
